
Overview of noun rigour

The noun rigour has 3 senses (no senses from tagged texts)
                                       
1. cogency, validity, rigor, rigour -- (the quality of being valid and rigorous)
2. asperity, grimness, hardship, rigor, rigour, severity, severeness, rigorousness, rigourousness -- (something hard to endure; "the asperity of northern winters")
3. severity, severeness, harshness, rigor, rigour, rigorousness, rigourousness, inclemency, hardness, stiffness -- (excessive sternness; "severity of character"; "the harshness of his punishment was inhuman"; "the rigors of boot camp")
